              <div type="translation">
<p>Hail! Elapsed Śaka year 749, month of Jyeṣṭha, eighth <foreign>tithi</foreign> of the waxing fortnight, Tuesday, Tuṅle (?), Pahiṅ. That was when the wife of <foreign>ḍaṅ</foreign> Puhavaṅ Gəlis, <supplied reason="explanation">named</supplied> <gap reason="ellipsis"/> 
<list>
<item>1 <gap reason="ellipsis"/></item>
<item>1 <foreign>damar</foreign> box</item>
<item>4 deity paddy boxes</item>
<item>1 <foreign>curi</foreign></item>
</list>

Such were the tokens of devotion of <foreign>ḍaṅ</foreign> Puhavaṅ Gəlis.

The witnesses to it were: <foreign>ḍa punta</foreign> Lākha; 
<foreign>ḍa punta</foreign> <gap reason="ellipsis"/>, hyaṅ guru gavai, 

It was written <gap reason="ellipsis"/> along with him.
It was made <foreign>ḍaṅ</foreign> Puhavaṅ Gəlis, as a mark of his not forgetting his benefice.
</p>
</div>
